    "This relatively high efficiency of dielectric metasurfaces comes at the cost of difficult fabrication, which will be discussed in Section \"Fabrication complexity and 3D alignment requirements\".",
    "Briefly, commonly used dielectric materials such as TiO 2 and Si are produced by slow and costly methods such as ALD and CVD.",
    "Realization of multilayer metasurface designs by these high-temperature processes, which preclude organic layer-to-layer spacers, is also difficult.",
    "Therefore, we believe that there are still tremendous opportunities in the discovery of low-loss, high-index optical materials that allow simpler fabrication.",
    "The dielectric nanoposts with small diameters typically have a very high aspect ratio that makes their accurate nanofabrication challenging, and therefore, the experimental diffraction efficiency can be compromised due to fabrication imperfections."
